    pearls: ["PALM-COEIN is the FIGO classification system for AUB: PALM (structural causes diagnosed by imaging/histology) = Polyp, Adenomyosis, Leiomyoma, Malignancy; COEIN (non-structural causes diagnosed by laboratory/history) = Coagulopathy, Ovulatory dysfunction, Endometrial, Iatrogenic, Not yet classified","Multiple PALM-COEIN categories can coexist in the same patient; a woman may have both fibroids (AUB-L) and von Willebrand disease (AUB-C), requiring treatment of both conditions","Postmenopausal bleeding is endometrial cancer until proven otherwise: any bleeding after 12 months of amenorrhea requires urgent endometrial biopsy and transvaginal ultrasound","The LNG-IUD (levonorgestrel intrauterine device) is first-line medical management for heavy menstrual bleeding from multiple etiologies and is equivalent to endometrial ablation in efficacy at 2 years with the advantage of reversibility","Screening for coagulopathy should be performed in all adolescents presenting with heavy menstrual bleeding at menarche and in any woman with HMB since menarche, easy bruising, family history of bleeding, or postpartum hemorrhage"],
